paper_metadata.title: MAIN TEXT
paper_metadata.extraction_summary: The paper discusses BRCA2 variants, specifically focusing on the 6174delT variant, and provides penetrance data related to affected and unaffected carriers.

patients.demographics: Not specified in detail, but includes both men and women of Ashkenazi Jewish descent.

functional_data.summary: The variant is associated with increased risk for breast and ovarian cancer.

variants.population_frequency: Approximately 1 in 401 in the Ashkenazi Jewish population.
variants.additional_notes: The variant is one of the three common founder variants in the Ashkenazi Jewish population.
key_quotes: Among individuals of Ashkenazi Jewish descent, three BRCA1/2 founder variants — 185delAG (c.68_69delAG), 5382insC (c.5266dupC), and 6174delT (c.5946delT) — are present at a frequency of ~1 in 401.

extraction_metadata.notes: Only one BRCA2 variant was identified in the paper.
